      | &nbsp;is a puzzle game where you must solve a crossword consisting of clues given in the form of regular expressions.
    // more
    p
      | The idea to make Regex Crossword came from the MIT Mystery Hunt, which featured a very difficult&nbsp;
      a(href='http://www.coinheist.com/rubik/a_regular_crossword/grid.pdf', target='_blank') multi-dimensional regular expression crossword
      | .&nbsp;
      a(href='http://hpcomic.wordpress.com') Maria Hagsten Pedersen
      | &nbsp;and I thought this was a really fun variation on the normal crossword and soduku-like puzzles, so we decided to create a game with more puzzles and easier difficulty levels, so newcomers could also have a fun way to learn regular expressions.
    p
      | The site is developed in JavaScript as a single-page app, using some great libraries like&nbsp;
      a(href='http://jquery.com') jQuery
      | &nbsp;and the MVC framework&nbsp;
      a(href='http://angularjs.org/') AngularJS
      | &nbsp;which also handles templating and routing with HTML5 pushState. I decided to use&nbsp;
      a(href='http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/index.html') Twitter Bootstrap
      | &nbsp;(and&nbsp;
      a(href='http://lesscss.org/') LESS
      | ) to implement a responsive design, where the interface will automatically adapt to different resolutions, like on the iPad and iPhone.
    p
      | Players can log into Facebook to save their progress and post achievements to their wall when completing a set of crossword puzzles. To save the players progress I created a simple&nbsp;
      a(href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Representational_state_transfer') REST
      | -based key-value storage using PHP and MySQL.
